commit.message:
Add warning about interfering hotkeys

Closes #202.

Mention that braces can be escaped

Closes #184.

Add SXHKD_PID environment variable

This allows the SXHKD_SHELL process to send signals to the parent sxhkd
process, for instance to break a chain by sending SIGALRM.  This was
previously difficult due to the double fork preventing the use of the
$PPID environment variable.

Closes #284.
Closes #170.

Readme: add link to Emacs' `sxhkd-mode`

Closes #280.

Sequences can't be nested

This reverts commit 3b5298d35592380f66ec01247f222f01f6176833.

Closes #49.
Mention the fact that the sequences can be nested
